                            <comment id="16105718" author="tripod" created="Fri, 28 Jul 2017 21:29:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;how did you create the package? if it is created via the vlt api, then it should not create this file name, and is a bug. if it is created with an external tool, then the tool is buggy. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16109580" author="wmcgaule" created="Tue, 1 Aug 2017 19:26:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tripod&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tripod&quot;&gt;tripod&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The same thing happens when creating a package using AEM package manager with this same content and then importing on another AEM instance - appears to be something wrong with the vlt API.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16126834" author="tripod" created="Tue, 15 Aug 2017 05:52:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;another problem is that filenames with the pattern: &quot;&lt;em&gt;x1234&lt;/em&gt;&quot; are turned into their unicode equivalent.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
